\section{Results}\label{results}
The basic data products consist of data cubes, moment maps, integrated spectra, and 3D visualization for the group as a whole, as well as source catalogues, cubelettes, 
moment maps, position velocity cuts, and integrated spectra for each source detected by SoFiA. Figure~\ref{figure:data-products} shows examples of data products for NGC~1622 at \SI{43.8}{\arcsecond} $\times$ \SI{47.5}{\arcsecond} resolution, a spiral galaxy in HCG~30. Below we describe the data 
for the individual groups. In general, we detected even more extended tidal features for phase 2 groups than previously observed. For phase 3 groups, 
we did not detect any diffuse \HI\ component, but we detected some new high surface brightness features. In HCG~97 and HCG~91 we detected many 
galaxies surrounding the group center, suggesting that the groups are embedded in larger structures. Some of the detected galaxies do not have optical counterparts. 
% The difference between phase 2 and 3 groups is still abrupt, suggesting a rapid phase transition.  Should be in Lourdes paper
% Figure commented
